WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:11.120
Hi, my name is Tracy Thiel, and I am teaching the It's Not Just Code, Managing an Open Source

00:00:11.120 --> 00:00:13.880
Project at PawsitConf 2023.

00:00:13.880 --> 00:00:18.080
I am super excited about this workshop, and I want to tell you the top three reasons you

00:00:18.080 --> 00:00:20.000
should come to this workshop.

00:00:20.000 --> 00:00:23.500
The first is right there in the name, It's Not Just Code.

00:00:23.500 --> 00:00:28.280
We have a lot of great things at PawsitConf, a lot of them are around code, but if you've

00:00:28.280 --> 00:00:33.160
worked on an open source project, you've noticed that some of the things that are hard

00:00:33.160 --> 00:00:39.240
are really not about the code, but about collaboration, and project management, and governance.

00:00:39.240 --> 00:00:44.000
And those are things that we can learn too, you just usually haven't had an opportunity

00:00:44.000 --> 00:00:45.360
to learn them yet.

00:00:45.360 --> 00:00:50.040
So this is a place where you can learn about those other pieces of the projects that aren't

00:00:50.040 --> 00:00:51.040
the code.

00:00:51.040 --> 00:00:55.220
The second is templates, yes, templates.

00:00:55.220 --> 00:00:59.419
The thing that you're trying to do, other people have done it before, so you don't need

00:00:59.419 --> 00:01:01.580
to do it all on your own.

00:01:01.580 --> 00:01:05.860
And in this workshop, I'm going to give you templates, and workflows, and checklists that

00:01:05.860 --> 00:01:09.260
you can adapt for your project and get started with right away.

00:01:09.260 --> 00:01:14.980
Whether your project is big or small, just starting out has been there a while, you founded

00:01:14.980 --> 00:01:19.540
the project, or you're coming in new and want to contribute.

00:01:19.540 --> 00:01:22.779
These pieces will help you no matter where you are.

00:01:22.779 --> 00:01:26.260
And finally, the third is community.

00:01:26.260 --> 00:01:32.099
So this is an opportunity to come together with other like-minded folks.

00:01:32.099 --> 00:01:36.339
If you're in this place in a project that can feel a little bit lonely, you know, maybe

00:01:36.339 --> 00:01:40.300
don't have somebody else to talk to, you're not sure if the things that you think are

00:01:40.300 --> 00:01:46.339
hard are just hard overall, or something that you feel like you're not good at.

00:01:46.339 --> 00:01:51.260
This is a place where you can talk to other people about shared challenges, build some

00:01:51.260 --> 00:01:56.940
networks, or community, and have these kinds of connections with people that are things

00:01:56.940 --> 00:02:01.419
that you can talk about going forward, or even just in the workshop.

00:02:01.419 --> 00:02:03.419
So I hope to see you there.

00:02:03.419 --> 00:02:07.519
I'm so excited about all the things that we'll get to talk about in this workshop, and the

00:02:07.519 --> 00:02:13.220
ways that they are going to make your life as a maintainer, a manager, or anyone involved

00:02:13.220 --> 00:02:17.300
in an open source project better and more sustainable.

00:02:17.300 --> 00:02:17.979
Hope to see you there.

